finding.evidence:
This session has tool "mcp__ide__getDiagnostics" visible in the tool list. Pattern: mcp__{server-name}__{tool-name}
Our server "file-ops" would produce: mcp__file-ops__file_read mcp__file-ops__file_edit mcp__file-ops__file_write mcp__file-ops__file_insert mcp__file-ops__file_search mcp__file-ops__file_structure
Built-in tools use simple names: Read, Edit, Write, Grep, Glob CONCLUSION: Zero naming conflicts possible. Prefix ensures separation.

Existing registration confirmed at ~/.claude/settings.json: "skill-router": {"command": "python", "args": ["path/to/server.py"]}
Three scopes available: local (default, per-project), project (shared via .mcp.json), user (all projects, ~/.claude.json)
For our use case: user scope makes sense (available in all projects)

